  <bioghist id="aspace_0cd1f5ed4a6b2d534b3c10f5bd89b642">
    <head>BIOGRAPHICAL NOTE</head>
<p>Methodist minister.</p>  </bioghist>
  <scopecontent id="aspace_928c333c5f335c0b68db6765ee0de901">
    <head>COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
<p>Papers of George Frederick Wells include diaries, 1905-1958; writings on the rural church and various theological questions; sermons; scrapbooks and notebooks; and pamphlets, tracts and church programs. Also, correspondence, 1900-1958, much of it with World War II servicemen, but also concerning the Country Church Movement.</p>  </scopecontent>
